page.title: 01Introduction to Felixstowe
page.content: Felixstowe is a famous seaside town on the East coast and it has a lot of day trippers during the summer.A large proportion of Felixstowe is taken up by the docks. Felixstowe has a population of about 22,500 and many other people are coming to live there because of the expanding docks.There are a lot of new buildings being built,including The Great Eastern Square,the new swimming pool and the Cavendish Park estate near to the docks.Retired people often come to Felixstowe as it is a quiet seaside town. {
